notesStmt.note: Manuscript description based on Margoliouth, G.: Catalogue of the Hebrew and Samaritan Manuscripts in the British Museum, London 1965.

layoutDesc.layout: Columns: 1 2; ruled lines: 26 38; written lines: 26 38; Uniform layout. Visible pencil ruling. Titles and inital words in larger square characters. Catchwords on every page or under each column.

scriptDesc.scriptNote: Sefardi square and semi-cursive script of the 18th century. Yeḥezkel ben Shemu᾿el Kohen: inscribed with his name in the colophon, folio 72v, and given in acrostics, folio 1v, 40r.

binding.p: Post-1600. Brown leather, gold tooled. Spine: 'Al-Gazali. Tractatus De Logica. Hebraice. Mus Brit. Jure Emptionis. 18,971.'

history.provenance: Acquisition: Adolphus Asher (b. 1800, d. 1853), Berlin bookseller and dealer to the British Museum 1841-1853: purchased from him on 12 June 1852; inscribed, folio [73v] (fse001v).
